  <discussion type="conservation">of conservation concern;</discussion>
  <discussion>Variety gossypina is known only from the San Bernardino Mountains, southern California. It is recognized by its tufted-tomentose pubescence, long involucres, unequal phyllaries, and geographic isolation.</discussion>
